{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":888,"text":"Chris Anderson: Hello.\nWelcome to this TED Dialogues."},{"time":4666,"text":"It's the first of a series\nthat's going to be done"},{"time":8277,"text":"in response to the current\npolitical upheaval."},{"time":12265,"text":"I don't know about you;"},{"time":13458,"text":"I've become quite concerned about\nthe growing divisiveness in this country"},{"time":17093,"text":"and in the world."},{"time":18613,"text":"No one's listening to each other. Right?"},{"time":21564,"text":"They aren't."},{"time":22751,"text":"I mean, it feels like we need\na different kind of conversation,"},{"time":26511,"text":"one that's based on -- I don't know,\non reason, listening, on understanding,"},{"time":32463,"text":"on a broader context."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34840,"text":"That's at least what we're going to try\nin these TED Dialogues,"},{"time":37891,"text":"starting today."},{"time":39107,"text":"And we couldn't have anyone with us"},{"time":41757,"text":"who I'd be more excited to kick this off."},{"time":44590,"text":"This is a mind right here that thinks\npretty much like no one else"},{"time":48464,"text":"on the planet, I would hasten to say."},{"time":50259,"text":"I'm serious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51442,"text":"(Yuval Noah Harari laughs)"},{"time":52728,"text":"I'm serious."},{"time":53916,"text":"He synthesizes history\nwith underlying ideas"},{"time":58878,"text":"in a way that kind of takes\nyour breath away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61072,"text":"So, some of you will know\nthis book, \"Sapiens.\""},{"time":64505,"text":"Has anyone here read \"Sapiens\"?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":66272,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":67508,"text":"I mean, I could not put it down."},{"time":70677,"text":"The way that he tells the story of mankind"},{"time":74575,"text":"through big ideas that really make you\nthink differently --"},{"time":78401,"text":"it's kind of amazing."},{"time":80160,"text":"And here's the follow-up,"},{"time":81408,"text":"which I think is being published\nin the US next week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84508,"text":"YNH: Yeah, next week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85683,"text":"CA: \"Homo Deus.\""},{"time":86881,"text":"Now, this is the history\nof the next hundred years."},{"time":90521,"text":"I've had a chance to read it."},{"time":92395,"text":"It's extremely dramatic,"},{"time":94809,"text":"and I daresay, for some people,\nquite alarming."},{"time":99605,"text":"It's a must-read."},{"time":100872,"text":"And honestly, we couldn't have\nsomeone better to help"},{"time":106474,"text":"make sense of what on Earth\nis happening in the world right now."},{"time":110474,"text":"So a warm welcome, please,\nto Yuval Noah Harari."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114655,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":122900,"text":"It's great to be joined by our friends\non Facebook and around the Web."},{"time":126669,"text":"Hello, Facebook."},{"time":128270,"text":"And all of you, as I start\nasking questions of Yuval,"},{"time":132220,"text":"come up with your own questions,"},{"time":133896,"text":"and not necessarily about\nthe political scandal du jour,"},{"time":136567,"text":"but about the broader understanding\nof: Where are we heading?"},{"time":142517,"text":"You ready? OK, we're going to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144307,"text":"So here we are, Yuval:"},{"time":145606,"text":"New York City, 2017,\nthere's a new president in power,"},{"time":149350,"text":"and shock waves rippling around the world."},{"time":152495,"text":"What on Earth is happening?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":155115,"text":"YNH: I think the basic thing that happened"},{"time":157385,"text":"is that we have lost our story."},{"time":160144,"text":"Humans think in stories,"},{"time":162635,"text":"and we try to make sense of the world\nby telling stories."},{"time":166321,"text":"And for the last few decades,"},{"time":167762,"text":"we had a very simple\nand very attractive story"},{"time":170656,"text":"about what's happening in the world."},{"time":172429,"text":"And the story said that,\noh, what's happening is"},{"time":175617,"text":"that the economy is being globalized,"},{"time":178257,"text":"politics is being liberalized,"},{"time":180424,"text":"and the combination of the two\nwill create paradise on Earth,"},{"time":184447,"text":"and we just need to keep on\nglobalizing the economy"},{"time":187570,"text":"and liberalizing the political system,"},{"time":189405,"text":"and everything will be wonderful."},{"time":191334,"text":"And 2016 is the moment"},{"time":194090,"text":"when a very large segment,\neven of the Western world,"},{"time":198074,"text":"stopped believing in this story."},{"time":200504,"text":"For good or bad reasons --\nit doesn't matter."},{"time":202660,"text":"People stopped believing in the story,"},{"time":204905,"text":"and when you don't have a story,\nyou don't understand what's happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209212,"text":"CA: Part of you believes that that story\nwas actually a very effective story."},{"time":213203,"text":"It worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214421,"text":"YNH: To some extent, yes."},{"time":215922,"text":"According to some measurements,"},{"time":218008,"text":"we are now in the best time ever"},{"time":220617,"text":"for humankind."},{"time":222068,"text":"Today, for the first time in history,"},{"time":224532,"text":"more people die from eating too much\nthan from eating too little,"},{"time":228969,"text":"which is an amazing achievement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230765,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":233472,"text":"Also for the first time in history,"},{"time":235197,"text":"more people die from old age\nthan from infectious diseases,"},{"time":239356,"text":"and violence is also down."},{"time":242174,"text":"For the first time in history,"},{"time":243628,"text":"more people commit suicide\nthan are killed by crime and terrorism"},{"time":248983,"text":"and war put together."},{"time":250847,"text":"Statistically, you are\nyour own worst enemy."},{"time":255031,"text":"At least, of all the people in the world,"},{"time":257061,"text":"you are most likely\nto be killed by yourself --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":260207,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":261498,"text":"which is, again,\nvery good news, compared --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":264566,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266214,"text":"compared to the level of violence\nthat we saw in previous eras."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270539,"text":"CA: But this process\nof connecting the world"},{"time":272799,"text":"ended up with a large group of people\nkind of feeling left out,"},{"time":276722,"text":"and they've reacted."},{"time":278377,"text":"And so we have this bombshell"},{"time":280387,"text":"that's sort of ripping\nthrough the whole system."},{"time":282722,"text":"I mean, what do you make\nof what's happened?"},{"time":286138,"text":"It feels like the old way\nthat people thought of politics,"},{"time":289440,"text":"the left-right divide,\nhas been blown up and replaced."},{"time":292320,"text":"How should we think of this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293941,"text":"YNH: Yeah, the old 20th-century\npolitical model of left versus right"},{"time":298349,"text":"is now largely irrelevant,"},{"time":300080,"text":"and the real divide today\nis between global and national,"},{"time":304606,"text":"global or local."},{"time":306419,"text":"And you see it again all over the world"},{"time":309300,"text":"that this is now the main struggle."},{"time":311469,"text":"We probably need completely\nnew political models"},{"time":314929,"text":"and completely new ways\nof thinking about politics."},{"time":320499,"text":"In essence, what you can say\nis that we now have global ecology,"},{"time":326053,"text":"we have a global economy\nbut we have national politics,"},{"time":330018,"text":"and this doesn't work together."},{"time":331779,"text":"This makes the political\nsystem ineffective,"},{"time":334029,"text":"because it has no control\nover the forces that shape our life."},{"time":337577,"text":"And you have basically two solutions\nto this imbalance:"},{"time":340880,"text":"either de-globalize the economy\nand turn it back into a national economy,"},{"time":345478,"text":"or globalize the political system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348948,"text":"CA: So some, I guess\nmany liberals out there"},{"time":353637,"text":"view Trump and his government\nas kind of irredeemably bad,"},{"time":360097,"text":"just awful in every way."},{"time":362780,"text":"Do you see any underlying narrative\nor political philosophy in there"},{"time":369227,"text":"that is at least worth understanding?"},{"time":371055,"text":"How would you articulate that philosophy?"},{"time":373124,"text":"Is it just the philosophy of nationalism?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":376254,"text":"YNH: I think the underlying\nfeeling or idea"},{"time":381678,"text":"is that the political system --\nsomething is broken there."},{"time":386194,"text":"It doesn't empower\nthe ordinary person anymore."},{"time":389988,"text":"It doesn't care so much\nabout the ordinary person anymore,"},{"time":393512,"text":"and I think this diagnosis\nof the political disease is correct."},{"time":398355,"text":"With regard to the answers,\nI am far less certain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401738,"text":"I think what we are seeing\nis the immediate human reaction:"},{"time":405245,"text":"if something doesn't work, let's go back."},{"time":407827,"text":"And you see it all over the world,"},{"time":409472,"text":"that people, almost nobody\nin the political system today,"},{"time":413922,"text":"has any future-oriented vision\nof where humankind is going."},{"time":418139,"text":"Almost everywhere,\nyou see retrograde vision:"},{"time":421189,"text":"\"Let's make America great again,\""},{"time":423259,"text":"like it was great -- I don't know --\nin the '50s, in the '80s, sometime,"},{"time":426712,"text":"let's go back there."},{"time":427906,"text":"And you go to Russia\na hundred years after Lenin,"},{"time":432651,"text":"Putin's vision for the future"},{"time":434546,"text":"is basically, ah, let's go back\nto the Tsarist empire."},{"time":437767,"text":"And in Israel, where I come from,"},{"time":440183,"text":"the hottest political vision\nof the present is:"},{"time":443459,"text":"\"Let's build the temple again.\""},{"time":445334,"text":"So let's go back 2,000 years backwards."},{"time":448336,"text":"So people are thinking\nsometime in the past we've lost it,"},{"time":453186,"text":"and sometimes in the past, it's like\nyou've lost your way in the city,"},{"time":456948,"text":"and you say OK, let's go back\nto the point where I felt secure"},{"time":460122,"text":"and start again."},{"time":461508,"text":"I don't think this can work,"},{"time":463105,"text":"but a lot of people,\nthis is their gut instinct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466031,"text":"CA: But why couldn't it work?"},{"time":467707,"text":"\"America First\" is a very\nappealing slogan in many ways."},{"time":471370,"text":"Patriotism is, in many ways,\na very noble thing."},{"time":475271,"text":"It's played a role\nin promoting cooperation"},{"time":478036,"text":"among large numbers of people."},{"time":479650,"text":"Why couldn't you have a world\norganized in countries,"},{"time":483556,"text":"all of which put themselves first?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":487373,"text":"YNH: For many centuries,\neven thousands of years,"},{"time":490716,"text":"patriotism worked quite well."},{"time":493502,"text":"Of course, it led to wars an so forth,"},{"time":495405,"text":"but we shouldn't focus\ntoo much on the bad."},{"time":498384,"text":"There are also many,\nmany positive things about patriotism,"},{"time":501950,"text":"and the ability to have\na large number of people"},{"time":505748,"text":"care about each other,"},{"time":507186,"text":"sympathize with one another,"},{"time":508816,"text":"and come together for collective action."},{"time":512054,"text":"If you go back to the first nations,"},{"time":514773,"text":"so, thousands of years ago,"},{"time":516622,"text":"the people who lived along\nthe Yellow River in China --"},{"time":520052,"text":"it was many, many different tribes"},{"time":522519,"text":"and they all depended on the river\nfor survival and for prosperity,"},{"time":526913,"text":"but all of them also suffered\nfrom periodical floods"},{"time":531246,"text":"and periodical droughts."},{"time":532870,"text":"And no tribe could really do\nanything about it,"},{"time":535929,"text":"because each of them controlled\njust a tiny section of the river."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540113,"text":"And then in a long\nand complicated process,"},{"time":542901,"text":"the tribes coalesced together\nto form the Chinese nation,"},{"time":546849,"text":"which controlled the entire Yellow River"},{"time":549507,"text":"and had the ability to bring\nhundreds of thousands of people together"},{"time":554978,"text":"to build dams and canals\nand regulate the river"},{"time":559253,"text":"and prevent the worst floods and droughts"},{"time":562464,"text":"and raise the level\nof prosperity for everybody."},{"time":565588,"text":"And this worked in many places\naround the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568229,"text":"But in the 21st century,"},{"time":571379,"text":"technology is changing all that\nin a fundamental way."},{"time":574838,"text":"We are now living -- all people\nin the world --"},{"time":577576,"text":"are living alongside the same cyber river,"},{"time":581417,"text":"and no single nation can regulate\nthis river by itself."},{"time":587047,"text":"We are all living together\non a single planet,"},{"time":591114,"text":"which is threatened by our own actions."},{"time":593899,"text":"And if you don't have some kind\nof global cooperation,"},{"time":597939,"text":"nationalism is just not on the right level\nto tackle the problems,"},{"time":603106,"text":"whether it's climate change\nor whether it's technological disruption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607761,"text":"CA: So it was a beautiful idea"},{"time":609976,"text":"in a world where most of the action,\nmost of the issues,"},{"time":613948,"text":"took place on national scale,"},{"time":616328,"text":"but your argument is that the issues\nthat matter most today"},{"time":619150,"text":"no longer take place on a national scale\nbut on a global scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622318,"text":"YNH: Exactly. All the major problems\nof the world today"},{"time":626151,"text":"are global in essence,"},{"time":628564,"text":"and they cannot be solved"},{"time":630079,"text":"unless through some kind\nof global cooperation."},{"time":634000,"text":"It's not just climate change,"},{"time":635653,"text":"which is, like, the most obvious\nexample people give."},{"time":639081,"text":"I think more in terms\nof technological disruption."},{"time":642183,"text":"If you think about, for example,\nartificial intelligence,"},{"time":645257,"text":"over the next 20, 30 years"},{"time":648274,"text":"pushing hundreds of millions of people\nout of the job market --"},{"time":652182,"text":"this is a problem on a global level."},{"time":654457,"text":"It will disrupt the economy\nof all the countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657984,"text":"And similarly, if you think\nabout, say, bioengineering"},{"time":661671,"text":"and people being afraid of conducting,"},{"time":664650,"text":"I don't know, genetic engineering\nresearch in humans,"},{"time":667335,"text":"it won't help if just\na single country, let's say the US,"},{"time":672648,"text":"outlaws all genetic experiments in humans,"},{"time":675996,"text":"but China or North Korea\ncontinues to do it."},{"time":679650,"text":"So the US cannot solve it by itself,"},{"time":682414,"text":"and very quickly, the pressure on the US\nto do the same will be immense"},{"time":687321,"text":"because we are talking about\nhigh-risk, high-gain technologies."},{"time":692235,"text":"If somebody else is doing it,\nI can't allow myself to remain behind."},{"time":696967,"text":"The only way to have regulations,\neffective regulations,"},{"time":702679,"text":"on things like genetic engineering,"},{"time":704796,"text":"is to have global regulations."},{"time":706832,"text":"If you just have national regulations,\nnobody would like to stay behind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711894,"text":"CA: So this is really interesting."},{"time":713926,"text":"It seems to me that this may be one key"},{"time":715881,"text":"to provoking at least\na constructive conversation"},{"time":719377,"text":"between the different sides here,"},{"time":721074,"text":"because I think everyone can agree\nthat the start point"},{"time":724240,"text":"of a lot of the anger\nthat's propelled us to where we are"},{"time":726961,"text":"is because of the legitimate\nconcerns about job loss."},{"time":729733,"text":"Work is gone, a traditional\nway of life has gone,"},{"time":733398,"text":"and it's no wonder\nthat people are furious about that."},{"time":736797,"text":"And in general, they have blamed\nglobalism, global elites,"},{"time":741373,"text":"for doing this to them\nwithout asking their permission,"},{"time":744144,"text":"and that seems like\na legitimate complaint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746263,"text":"But what I hear you saying\nis that -- so a key question is:"},{"time":749596,"text":"What is the real cause of job loss,\nboth now and going forward?"},{"time":755081,"text":"To the extent that it's about globalism,"},{"time":757881,"text":"then the right response,\nyes, is to shut down borders"},{"time":762027,"text":"and keep people out\nand change trade agreements and so forth."},{"time":766031,"text":"But you're saying, I think,"},{"time":767411,"text":"that actually the bigger cause of job loss\nis not going to be that at all."},{"time":772226,"text":"It's going to originate\nin technological questions,"},{"time":775964,"text":"and we have no chance of solving that"},{"time":778000,"text":"unless we operate as a connected world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780119,"text":"YNH: Yeah, I think that,"},{"time":781662,"text":"I don't know about the present,\nbut looking to the future,"},{"time":784927,"text":"it's not the Mexicans or Chinese\nwho will take the jobs"},{"time":788028,"text":"from the people in Pennsylvania,"},{"time":789619,"text":"it's the robots and algorithms."},{"time":791386,"text":"So unless you plan to build a big wall\non the border of California --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":795594,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":796752,"text":"the wall on the border with Mexico\nis going to be very ineffective."},{"time":800467,"text":"And I was struck when I watched\nthe debates before the election,"},{"time":806839,"text":"I was struck that certainly Trump\ndid not even attempt to frighten people"},{"time":812600,"text":"by saying the robots will take your jobs."},{"time":815200,"text":"Now even if it's not true,\nit doesn't matter."},{"time":817523,"text":"It could have been an extremely\neffective way of frightening people --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":821065,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":822090,"text":"and galvanizing people:"},{"time":823275,"text":"\"The robots will take your jobs!\""},{"time":824908,"text":"And nobody used that line."},{"time":826287,"text":"And it made me afraid,"},{"time":829003,"text":"because it meant\nthat no matter what happens"},{"time":833075,"text":"in universities and laboratories,"},{"time":835245,"text":"and there, there is already\nan intense debate about it,"},{"time":838034,"text":"but in the mainstream political system\nand among the general public,"},{"time":842152,"text":"people are just unaware"},{"time":844286,"text":"that there could be an immense\ntechnological disruption --"},{"time":848820,"text":"not in 200 years,\nbut in 10, 20, 30 years --"},{"time":852966,"text":"and we have to do something about it now,"},{"time":855560,"text":"partly because most of what we teach\nchildren today in school or in college"},{"time":861860,"text":"is going to be completely irrelevant\nto the job market of 2040, 2050."},{"time":867885,"text":"So it's not something we'll need\nto think about in 2040."},{"time":871267,"text":"We need to think today\nwhat to teach the young people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874884,"text":"CA: Yeah, no, absolutely."},{"time":878595,"text":"You've often written about\nmoments in history"},{"time":882536,"text":"where humankind has ...\nentered a new era, unintentionally."},{"time":889806,"text":"Decisions have been made,\ntechnologies have been developed,"},{"time":892698,"text":"and suddenly the world has changed,"},{"time":895093,"text":"possibly in a way\nthat's worse for everyone."},{"time":897584,"text":"So one of the examples\nyou give in \"Sapiens\""},{"time":899683,"text":"is just the whole agricultural revolution,"},{"time":901798,"text":"which, for an actual person\ntilling the fields,"},{"time":905376,"text":"they just picked up a 12-hour\nbackbreaking workday"},{"time":908580,"text":"instead of six hours in the jungle\nand a much more interesting lifestyle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":914852,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":915918,"text":"So are we at another possible\nphase change here,"},{"time":919131,"text":"where we kind of sleepwalk into a future\nthat none of us actually wants?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":924058,"text":"YNH: Yes, very much so."},{"time":926815,"text":"During the agricultural revolution,"},{"time":928676,"text":"what happened is that immense\ntechnological and economic revolution"},{"time":933120,"text":"empowered the human collective,"},{"time":936009,"text":"but when you look at actual\nindividual lives,"},{"time":938986,"text":"the life of a tiny elite\nbecame much better,"},{"time":942504,"text":"and the lives of the majority of people\nbecame considerably worse."},{"time":946766,"text":"And this can happen again\nin the 21st century."},{"time":949495,"text":"No doubt the new technologies\nwill empower the human collective."},{"time":954385,"text":"But we may end up again"},{"time":957129,"text":"with a tiny elite reaping\nall the benefits, taking all the fruits,"},{"time":961610,"text":"and the masses of the population\nfinding themselves worse"},{"time":965820,"text":"than they were before,"},{"time":967145,"text":"certainly much worse than this tiny elite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970657,"text":"CA: And those elites\nmight not even be human elites."},{"time":973336,"text":"They might be cyborgs or --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":975117,"text":"YNH: Yeah, they could be\nenhanced super humans."},{"time":977348,"text":"They could be cyborgs."},{"time":978627,"text":"They could be completely\nnonorganic elites."},{"time":981008,"text":"They could even be\nnon-conscious algorithms."},{"time":983560,"text":"What we see now in the world\nis authority shifting away"},{"time":988495,"text":"from humans to algorithms."},{"time":990788,"text":"More and more decisions --\nabout personal lives,"},{"time":994336,"text":"about economic matters,\nabout political matters --"},{"time":997032,"text":"are actually being taken by algorithms."},{"time":999535,"text":"If you ask the bank for a loan,"},{"time":1002193,"text":"chances are your fate is decided\nby an algorithm, not by a human being."},{"time":1006914,"text":"And the general impression\nis that maybe Homo sapiens just lost it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1013125,"text":"The world is so complicated,\nthere is so much data,"},{"time":1017709,"text":"things are changing so fast,"},{"time":1020287,"text":"that this thing that evolved\non the African savanna"},{"time":1023912,"text":"tens of thousands of years ago --"},{"time":1025643,"text":"to cope with a particular environment,"},{"time":1029164,"text":"a particular volume\nof information and data --"},{"time":1032672,"text":"it just can't handle the realities\nof the 21st century,"},{"time":1037032,"text":"and the only thing\nthat may be able to handle it"},{"time":1039953,"text":"is big-data algorithms."},{"time":1042049,"text":"So no wonder more and more authority\nis shifting from us to the algorithms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1048857,"text":"CA: So we're in New York City\nfor the first of a series of TED Dialogues"},{"time":1052730,"text":"with Yuval Harari,"},{"time":1055051,"text":"and there's a Facebook Live\naudience out there."},{"time":1058919,"text":"We're excited to have you with us."},{"time":1060594,"text":"We'll start coming\nto some of your questions"},{"time":1062720,"text":"and questions of people in the room"},{"time":1064458,"text":"in just a few minutes,"},{"time":1065647,"text":"so have those coming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1067635,"text":"Yuval, if you're going\nto make the argument"},{"time":1071556,"text":"that we need to get past nationalism\nbecause of the coming technological ..."},{"time":1079218,"text":"danger, in a way,"},{"time":1081083,"text":"presented by so much of what's happening"},{"time":1083052,"text":"we've got to have\na global conversation about this."},{"time":1085519,"text":"Trouble is, it's hard to get people\nreally believing that, I don't know,"},{"time":1088971,"text":"AI really is an imminent\nthreat, and so forth."},{"time":1091156,"text":"The things that people,\nsome people at least,"},{"time":1093906,"text":"care about much more immediately, perhaps,"},{"time":1095965,"text":"is climate change,"},{"time":1097573,"text":"perhaps other issues like refugees,\nnuclear weapons, and so forth."},{"time":1102490,"text":"Would you argue that where\nwe are right now"},{"time":1107560,"text":"that somehow those issues\nneed to be dialed up?"},{"time":1111133,"text":"You've talked about climate change,"},{"time":1113317,"text":"but Trump has said\nhe doesn't believe in that."},{"time":1116997,"text":"So in a way, your most powerful argument,"},{"time":1119460,"text":"you can't actually use to make this case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1122230,"text":"YNH: Yeah, I think with climate change,"},{"time":1124440,"text":"at first sight, it's quite surprising"},{"time":1128171,"text":"that there is a very close correlation"},{"time":1130699,"text":"between nationalism and climate change."},{"time":1134045,"text":"I mean, almost always, the people\nwho deny climate change are nationalists."},{"time":1138656,"text":"And at first sight, you think: Why?"},{"time":1140761,"text":"What's the connection?"},{"time":1141938,"text":"Why don't you have socialists\ndenying climate change?"},{"time":1144748,"text":"But then, when you think\nabout it, it's obvious --"},{"time":1147123,"text":"because nationalism has no solution\nto climate change."},{"time":1150891,"text":"If you want to be a nationalist\nin the 21st century,"},{"time":1154111,"text":"you have to deny the problem."},{"time":1156007,"text":"If you accept the reality of the problem,\nthen you must accept that, yes,"},{"time":1160518,"text":"there is still room in the world\nfor patriotism,"},{"time":1163318,"text":"there is still room in the world\nfor having special loyalties"},{"time":1167493,"text":"and obligations towards your own people,\ntowards your own country."},{"time":1172151,"text":"I don't think anybody is really\nthinking of abolishing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1175995,"text":"But in order to confront climate change,"},{"time":1179020,"text":"we need additional loyalties\nand commitments"},{"time":1183255,"text":"to a level beyond the nation."},{"time":1185284,"text":"And that should not be impossible,"},{"time":1187751,"text":"because people can have\nseveral layers of loyalty."},{"time":1191467,"text":"You can be loyal to your family"},{"time":1193895,"text":"and to your community"},{"time":1195432,"text":"and to your nation,"},{"time":1196785,"text":"so why can't you also be loyal\nto humankind as a whole?"},{"time":1200437,"text":"Of course, there are occasions\nwhen it becomes difficult,"},{"time":1203860,"text":"what to put first,"},{"time":1205667,"text":"but, you know, life is difficult."},{"time":1207514,"text":"Handle it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1208689,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1211357,"text":"CA: OK, so I would love to get\nsome questions from the audience here."},{"time":1215879,"text":"We've got a microphone here."},{"time":1217821,"text":"Speak into it, and Facebook,\nget them coming, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1221062,"text":"Howard Morgan: One of the things that has\nclearly made a huge difference"},{"time":1224520,"text":"in this country and other countries"},{"time":1226330,"text":"is the income distribution inequality,"},{"time":1228568,"text":"the dramatic change\nin income distribution in the US"},{"time":1232806,"text":"from what it was 50 years ago,"},{"time":1234532,"text":"and around the world."},{"time":1235707,"text":"Is there anything we can do\nto affect that?"},{"time":1238874,"text":"Because that gets at a lot\nof the underlying causes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1244283,"text":"YNH: So far I haven't heard a very\ngood idea about what to do about it,"},{"time":1249621,"text":"again, partly because most ideas\nremain on the national level,"},{"time":1253373,"text":"and the problem is global."},{"time":1255165,"text":"I mean, one idea that we hear\nquite a lot about now"},{"time":1258167,"text":"is universal basic income."},{"time":1260023,"text":"But this is a problem."},{"time":1261198,"text":"I mean, I think it's a good start,"},{"time":1262874,"text":"but it's a problematic idea because\nit's not clear what \"universal\" is"},{"time":1266620,"text":"and it's not clear what \"basic\" is."},{"time":1268485,"text":"Most people when they speak\nabout universal basic income,"},{"time":1271890,"text":"they actually mean national basic income."},{"time":1274699,"text":"But the problem is global."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1276467,"text":"Let's say that you have AI and 3D printers\ntaking away millions of jobs"},{"time":1282141,"text":"in Bangladesh,"},{"time":1283321,"text":"from all the people who make\nmy shirts and my shoes."},{"time":1286593,"text":"So what's going to happen?"},{"time":1287923,"text":"The US government will levy taxes\non Google and Apple in California,"},{"time":1294486,"text":"and use that to pay basic income\nto unemployed Bangladeshis?"},{"time":1299091,"text":"If you believe that,\nyou can just as well believe"},{"time":1301751,"text":"that Santa Claus will come\nand solve the problem."},{"time":1305438,"text":"So unless we have really universal\nand not national basic income,"},{"time":1310588,"text":"the deep problems\nare not going to go away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1313747,"text":"And also it's not clear what basic is,"},{"time":1316503,"text":"because what are basic human needs?"},{"time":1319160,"text":"A thousand years ago,\njust food and shelter was enough."},{"time":1321994,"text":"But today, people will say\neducation is a basic human need,"},{"time":1325629,"text":"it should be part of the package."},{"time":1327226,"text":"But how much? Six years?\nTwelve years? PhD?"},{"time":1331029,"text":"Similarly, with health care,"},{"time":1332886,"text":"let's say that in 20, 30, 40 years,"},{"time":1335595,"text":"you'll have expensive treatments\nthat can extend human life"},{"time":1339392,"text":"to 120, I don't know."},{"time":1341331,"text":"Will this be part of the basket\nof basic income or not?"},{"time":1346546,"text":"It's a very difficult problem,"},{"time":1347999,"text":"because in a world where people\nlose their ability to be employed,"},{"time":1354281,"text":"the only thing they are going to get\nis this basic income."},{"time":1357886,"text":"So what's part of it is a very,\nvery difficult ethical question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1363037,"text":"CA: There's a bunch of questions\non how the world affords it as well,"},{"time":1366365,"text":"who pays."},{"time":1367549,"text":"There's a question here\nfrom Facebook from Lisa Larson:"},{"time":1370385,"text":"\"How does nationalism in the US now"},{"time":1372984,"text":"compare to that between\nWorld War I and World War II"},{"time":1376423,"text":"in the last century?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1377868,"text":"YNH: Well the good news, with regard\nto the dangers of nationalism,"},{"time":1382340,"text":"we are in a much better position\nthan a century ago."},{"time":1386287,"text":"A century ago, 1917,"},{"time":1388983,"text":"Europeans were killing\neach other by the millions."},{"time":1392140,"text":"In 2016, with Brexit,\nas far as I remember,"},{"time":1396515,"text":"a single person lost their life,\nan MP who was murdered by some extremist."},{"time":1401776,"text":"Just a single person."},{"time":1403333,"text":"I mean, if Brexit was about\nBritish independence,"},{"time":1406042,"text":"this is the most peaceful\nwar of independence in human history."},{"time":1410817,"text":"And let's say that Scotland\nwill now choose to leave the UK"},{"time":1416630,"text":"after Brexit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1418830,"text":"So in the 18th century,"},{"time":1420838,"text":"if Scotland wanted -- and the Scots\nwanted several times --"},{"time":1424094,"text":"to break out of the control of London,"},{"time":1427651,"text":"the reaction of the government\nin London was to send an army up north"},{"time":1431973,"text":"to burn down Edinburgh\nand massacre the highland tribes."},{"time":1435468,"text":"My guess is that if, in 2018,\nthe Scots vote for independence,"},{"time":1441048,"text":"the London government\nwill not send an army up north"},{"time":1444481,"text":"to burn down Edinburgh."},{"time":1446108,"text":"Very few people are now willing\nto kill or be killed"},{"time":1450399,"text":"for Scottish or for British independence."},{"time":1453145,"text":"So for all the talk\nof the rise of nationalism"},{"time":1458189,"text":"and going back to the 1930s,"},{"time":1460456,"text":"to the 19th century, in the West at least,"},{"time":1464255,"text":"the power of national sentiments\ntoday is far, far smaller"},{"time":1470863,"text":"than it was a century ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1472427,"text":"CA: Although some people now,\nyou hear publicly worrying"},{"time":1476288,"text":"about whether that might be shifting,"},{"time":1479068,"text":"that there could actually be\noutbreaks of violence in the US"},{"time":1482490,"text":"depending on how things turn out."},{"time":1484861,"text":"Should we be worried about that,"},{"time":1486424,"text":"or do you really think\nthings have shifted?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1488514,"text":"YNH: No, we should be worried."},{"time":1490029,"text":"We should be aware of two things."},{"time":1491678,"text":"First of all, don't be hysterical."},{"time":1493339,"text":"We are not back\nin the First World War yet."},{"time":1496810,"text":"But on the other hand,\ndon't be complacent."},{"time":1499774,"text":"We reached from 1917 to 2017,"},{"time":1505172,"text":"not by some divine miracle,"},{"time":1507378,"text":"but simply by human decisions,"},{"time":1509426,"text":"and if we now start making\nthe wrong decisions,"},{"time":1512113,"text":"we could be back\nin an analogous situation to 1917"},{"time":1516622,"text":"in a few years."},{"time":1518152,"text":"One of the things I know as a historian"},{"time":1520497,"text":"is that you should never\nunderestimate human stupidity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1524196,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1527103,"text":"It's one of the most powerful\nforces in history,"},{"time":1530211,"text":"human stupidity and human violence."},{"time":1532562,"text":"Humans do such crazy things\nfor no obvious reason,"},{"time":1536691,"text":"but again, at the same time,"},{"time":1538425,"text":"another very powerful force\nin human history is human wisdom."},{"time":1542053,"text":"We have both."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1543243,"text":"CA: We have with us here\nmoral psychologist Jonathan Haidt,"},{"time":1546169,"text":"who I think has a question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1548871,"text":"Jonathan Haidt: Thanks, Yuval."},{"time":1550378,"text":"So you seem to be a fan\nof global governance,"},{"time":1552885,"text":"but when you look at the map of the world\nfrom Transparency International,"},{"time":1556429,"text":"which rates the level of corruption\nof political institutions,"},{"time":1559781,"text":"it's a vast sea of red with little bits\nof yellow here and there"},{"time":1562885,"text":"for those with good institutions."},{"time":1564514,"text":"So if we were to have\nsome kind of global governance,"},{"time":1567039,"text":"what makes you think it would end up\nbeing more like Denmark"},{"time":1569894,"text":"rather than more like Russia or Honduras,"},{"time":1571958,"text":"and aren't there alternatives,"},{"time":1573483,"text":"such as we did with CFCs?"},{"time":1575593,"text":"There are ways to solve global problems\nwith national governments."},{"time":1578724,"text":"What would world government\nactually look like,"},{"time":1580962,"text":"and why do you think it would work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1582707,"text":"YNH: Well, I don't know\nwhat it would look like."},{"time":1586491,"text":"Nobody still has a model for that."},{"time":1589567,"text":"The main reason we need it"},{"time":1592219,"text":"is because many of these issues\nare lose-lose situations."},{"time":1596537,"text":"When you have\na win-win situation like trade,"},{"time":1599453,"text":"both sides can benefit\nfrom a trade agreement,"},{"time":1602393,"text":"then this is something you can work out."},{"time":1604681,"text":"Without some kind of global government,"},{"time":1607051,"text":"national governments each\nhave an interest in doing it."},{"time":1609929,"text":"But when you have a lose-lose situation\nlike with climate change,"},{"time":1613924,"text":"it's much more difficult"},{"time":1615589,"text":"without some overarching\nauthority, real authority."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1620499,"text":"Now, how to get there\nand what would it look like,"},{"time":1623285,"text":"I don't know."},{"time":1624669,"text":"And certainly there is no obvious reason"},{"time":1628430,"text":"to think that it would look like Denmark,"},{"time":1630734,"text":"or that it would be a democracy."},{"time":1632346,"text":"Most likely it wouldn't."},{"time":1634956,"text":"We don't have workable democratic models"},{"time":1641011,"text":"for a global government."},{"time":1643131,"text":"So maybe it would look more\nlike ancient China"},{"time":1646220,"text":"than like modern Denmark."},{"time":1647943,"text":"But still, given the dangers\nthat we are facing,"},{"time":1653190,"text":"I think the imperative of having\nsome kind of real ability"},{"time":1658334,"text":"to force through difficult decisions\non the global level"},{"time":1662486,"text":"is more important\nthan almost anything else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1667591,"text":"CA: There's a question from Facebook here,"},{"time":1669713,"text":"and then we'll get the mic to Andrew."},{"time":1671630,"text":"So, Kat Hebron on Facebook,"},{"time":1673850,"text":"calling in from Vail:"},{"time":1675542,"text":"\"How would developed nations manage\nthe millions of climate migrants?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1680818,"text":"YNH: I don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1682996,"text":"CA: That's your answer, Kat. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1684912,"text":"YNH: And I don't think\nthat they know either."},{"time":1687082,"text":"They'll just deny the problem, maybe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1688900,"text":"CA: But immigration, generally,\nis another example of a problem"},{"time":1691949,"text":"that's very hard to solve\non a nation-by-nation basis."},{"time":1694546,"text":"One nation can shut its doors,"},{"time":1696040,"text":"but maybe that stores up\nproblems for the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1698598,"text":"YNH: Yes, I mean --\nit's another very good case,"},{"time":1702494,"text":"especially because it's so much easier"},{"time":1704747,"text":"to migrate today"},{"time":1706602,"text":"than it was in the Middle Ages\nor in ancient times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1710315,"text":"CA: Yuval, there's a belief\namong many technologists, certainly,"},{"time":1714802,"text":"that political concerns\nare kind of overblown,"},{"time":1717177,"text":"that actually, political leaders\ndon't have that much influence"},{"time":1720898,"text":"in the world,"},{"time":1722088,"text":"that the real determination of humanity\nat this point is by science,"},{"time":1726081,"text":"by invention, by companies,"},{"time":1727551,"text":"by many things\nother than political leaders,"},{"time":1731967,"text":"and it's actually very hard\nfor leaders to do much,"},{"time":1734402,"text":"so we're actually worrying\nabout nothing here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1738005,"text":"YNH: Well, first, it should be emphasized"},{"time":1740265,"text":"that it's true that political leaders'\nability to do good is very limited,"},{"time":1745286,"text":"but their ability to do harm is unlimited."},{"time":1748353,"text":"There is a basic imbalance here."},{"time":1750977,"text":"You can still press the button\nand blow everybody up."},{"time":1754569,"text":"You have that kind of ability."},{"time":1756179,"text":"But if you want, for example,\nto reduce inequality,"},{"time":1759772,"text":"that's very, very difficult."},{"time":1761673,"text":"But to start a war,"},{"time":1763093,"text":"you can still do so very easily."},{"time":1764968,"text":"So there is a built-in imbalance\nin the political system today"},{"time":1768584,"text":"which is very frustrating,"},{"time":1770219,"text":"where you cannot do a lot of good\nbut you can still do a lot of harm."},{"time":1775144,"text":"And this makes the political system\nstill a very big concern."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1779812,"text":"CA: So as you look at\nwhat's happening today,"},{"time":1781987,"text":"and putting your historian's hat on,"},{"time":1783765,"text":"do you look back in history at moments\nwhen things were going just fine"},{"time":1787315,"text":"and an individual leader really took\nthe world or their country backwards?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1793307,"text":"YNH: There are quite a few examples,"},{"time":1795960,"text":"but I should emphasize,\nit's never an individual leader."},{"time":1798803,"text":"I mean, somebody put him there,"},{"time":1800461,"text":"and somebody allowed him\nto continue to be there."},{"time":1803768,"text":"So it's never really just the fault\nof a single individual."},{"time":1807875,"text":"There are a lot of people\nbehind every such individual."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1812512,"text":"CA: Can we have the microphone\nhere, please, to Andrew?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1819132,"text":"Andrew Solomon: You've talked a lot\nabout the global versus the national,"},{"time":1822720,"text":"but increasingly, it seems to me,"},{"time":1824370,"text":"the world situation\nis in the hands of identity groups."},{"time":1827037,"text":"We look at people within the United States"},{"time":1829371,"text":"who have been recruited by ISIS."},{"time":1831022,"text":"We look at these other groups\nwhich have formed"},{"time":1833237,"text":"which go outside of national bounds"},{"time":1835223,"text":"but still represent\nsignificant authorities."},{"time":1837408,"text":"How are they to be integrated\ninto the system,"},{"time":1839860,"text":"and how is a diverse set of identities\nto be made coherent"},{"time":1843597,"text":"under either national\nor global leadership?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1847380,"text":"YNH: Well, the problem\nof such diverse identities"},{"time":1850625,"text":"is a problem from nationalism as well."},{"time":1853229,"text":"Nationalism believes\nin a single, monolithic identity,"},{"time":1857608,"text":"and exclusive or at least\nmore extreme versions of nationalism"},{"time":1861748,"text":"believe in an exclusive loyalty\nto a single identity."},{"time":1865341,"text":"And therefore, nationalism has had\na lot of problems"},{"time":1868281,"text":"with people wanting to divide\ntheir identities"},{"time":1871181,"text":"between various groups."},{"time":1873268,"text":"So it's not just a problem, say,\nfor a global vision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1878540,"text":"And I think, again, history shows"},{"time":1882416,"text":"that you shouldn't necessarily\nthink in such exclusive terms."},{"time":1888567,"text":"If you think that there is just\na single identity for a person,"},{"time":1891999,"text":"\"I am just X, that's it, I can't be\nseveral things, I can be just that,\""},{"time":1897063,"text":"that's the start of the problem."},{"time":1899183,"text":"You have religions, you have nations"},{"time":1901995,"text":"that sometimes demand exclusive loyalty,"},{"time":1905201,"text":"but it's not the only option."},{"time":1906956,"text":"There are many religions and many nations"},{"time":1909362,"text":"that enable you to have\ndiverse identities at the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1913264,"text":"CA: But is one explanation\nof what's happened in the last year"},{"time":1917645,"text":"that a group of people have got\nfed up with, if you like,"},{"time":1922849,"text":"the liberal elites,\nfor want of a better term,"},{"time":1926040,"text":"obsessing over many, many different\nidentities and them feeling,"},{"time":1930437,"text":"\"But what about my identity?\nI am being completely ignored here."},{"time":1934320,"text":"And by the way, I thought\nI was the majority\"?"},{"time":1937318,"text":"And that that's actually\nsparked a lot of the anger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1940918,"text":"YNH: Yeah. Identity is always problematic,"},{"time":1944087,"text":"because identity is always based\non fictional stories"},{"time":1948421,"text":"that sooner or later collide with reality."},{"time":1951890,"text":"Almost all identities,"},{"time":1953432,"text":"I mean, beyond the level\nof the basic community"},{"time":1956867,"text":"of a few dozen people,"},{"time":1958360,"text":"are based on a fictional story."},{"time":1960313,"text":"They are not the truth."},{"time":1961978,"text":"They are not the reality."},{"time":1963317,"text":"It's just a story that people invent\nand tell one another"},{"time":1966435,"text":"and start believing."},{"time":1967950,"text":"And therefore all identities\nare extremely unstable."},{"time":1973294,"text":"They are not a biological reality."},{"time":1975845,"text":"Sometimes nationalists, for example,"},{"time":1977875,"text":"think that the nation\nis a biological entity."},{"time":1980826,"text":"It's made of the combination\nof soil and blood,"},{"time":1984463,"text":"creates the nation."},{"time":1986189,"text":"But this is just a fictional story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1989305,"text":"CA: Soil and blood\nkind of makes a gooey mess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1991892,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1993738,"text":"YNH: It does, and also\nit messes with your mind"},{"time":1996786,"text":"when you think too much\nthat I am a combination of soil and blood."},{"time":2001594,"text":"If you look from a biological perspective,"},{"time":2004485,"text":"obviously none of the nations\nthat exist today"},{"time":2007987,"text":"existed 5,000 years ago."},{"time":2010254,"text":"Homo sapiens is a social animal,\nthat's for sure."},{"time":2014136,"text":"But for millions of years,"},{"time":2016587,"text":"Homo sapiens and our hominid ancestors\nlived in small communities"},{"time":2021250,"text":"of a few dozen individuals."},{"time":2023603,"text":"Everybody knew everybody else."},{"time":2025754,"text":"Whereas modern nations\nare imagined communities,"},{"time":2029799,"text":"in the sense that I don't even know\nall these people."},{"time":2032374,"text":"I come from a relatively\nsmall nation, Israel,"},{"time":2035246,"text":"and of eight million Israelis,"},{"time":2037413,"text":"I never met most of them."},{"time":2039427,"text":"I will never meet most of them."},{"time":2041759,"text":"They basically exist here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2044345,"text":"CA: But in terms of this identity,"},{"time":2047118,"text":"this group who feel left out\nand perhaps have work taken away,"},{"time":2052579,"text":"I mean, in \"Homo Deus,\""},{"time":2054897,"text":"you actually speak of this group\nin one sense expanding,"},{"time":2058032,"text":"that so many people\nmay have their jobs taken away"},{"time":2061678,"text":"by technology in some way\nthat we could end up with"},{"time":2066082,"text":"a really large -- I think you call it\na \"useless class\" --"},{"time":2069277,"text":"a class where traditionally,"},{"time":2071404,"text":"as viewed by the economy,\nthese people have no use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2074159,"text":"YNH: Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2075381,"text":"CA: How likely a possibility is that?"},{"time":2078336,"text":"Is that something\nwe should be terrified about?"},{"time":2081104,"text":"And can we address it in any way?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2083787,"text":"YNH: We should think about it\nvery carefully."},{"time":2086058,"text":"I mean, nobody really knows\nwhat the job market will look like"},{"time":2089053,"text":"in 2040, 2050."},{"time":2090767,"text":"There is a chance\nmany new jobs will appear,"},{"time":2093499,"text":"but it's not certain."},{"time":2095277,"text":"And even if new jobs do appear,"},{"time":2097512,"text":"it won't necessarily be easy"},{"time":2099520,"text":"for a 50-year old unemployed truck driver"},{"time":2102543,"text":"made unemployed by self-driving vehicles,"},{"time":2105600,"text":"it won't be easy\nfor an unemployed truck driver"},{"time":2109277,"text":"to reinvent himself or herself\nas a designer of virtual worlds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2114087,"text":"Previously, if you look at the trajectory\nof the industrial revolution,"},{"time":2118293,"text":"when machines replaced humans\nin one type of work,"},{"time":2122474,"text":"the solution usually came\nfrom low-skill work"},{"time":2126779,"text":"in new lines of business."},{"time":2129391,"text":"So you didn't need any more\nagricultural workers,"},{"time":2132817,"text":"so people moved to working\nin low-skill industrial jobs,"},{"time":2138255,"text":"and when this was taken away\nby more and more machines,"},{"time":2141748,"text":"people moved to low-skill service jobs."},{"time":2144742,"text":"Now, when people say there will\nbe new jobs in the future,"},{"time":2148126,"text":"that humans can do better than AI,"},{"time":2150579,"text":"that humans can do better than robots,"},{"time":2152433,"text":"they usually think about high-skill jobs,"},{"time":2155097,"text":"like software engineers\ndesigning virtual worlds."},{"time":2158992,"text":"Now, I don't see how\nan unemployed cashier from Wal-Mart"},{"time":2164410,"text":"reinvents herself or himself at 50\nas a designer of virtual worlds,"},{"time":2169057,"text":"and certainly I don't see"},{"time":2170552,"text":"how the millions of unemployed\nBangladeshi textile workers"},{"time":2174043,"text":"will be able to do that."},{"time":2175678,"text":"I mean, if they are going to do it,"},{"time":2177422,"text":"we need to start teaching\nthe Bangladeshis today"},{"time":2180802,"text":"how to be software designers,"},{"time":2182580,"text":"and we are not doing it."},{"time":2183847,"text":"So what will they do in 20 years?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2186362,"text":"CA: So it feels like you're really\nhighlighting a question"},{"time":2190300,"text":"that's really been bugging me\nthe last few months more and more."},{"time":2194507,"text":"It's almost a hard question\nto ask in public,"},{"time":2197386,"text":"but if any mind has some wisdom\nto offer in it, maybe it's yours,"},{"time":2200801,"text":"so I'm going to ask you:"},{"time":2202370,"text":"What are humans for?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2205232,"text":"YNH: As far as we know, for nothing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2207190,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2208926,"text":"I mean, there is no great cosmic drama,\nsome great cosmic plan,"},{"time":2214476,"text":"that we have a role to play in."},{"time":2217341,"text":"And we just need to discover\nwhat our role is"},{"time":2220389,"text":"and then play it to the best\nof our ability."},{"time":2223405,"text":"This has been the story of all religions\nand ideologies and so forth,"},{"time":2228407,"text":"but as a scientist, the best I can say\nis this is not true."},{"time":2231909,"text":"There is no universal drama\nwith a role in it for Homo sapiens."},{"time":2237291,"text":"So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2238996,"text":"CA: I'm going to push back on you\njust for a minute,"},{"time":2241513,"text":"just from your own book,"},{"time":2242731,"text":"because in \"Homo Deus,\""},{"time":2244079,"text":"you give really one of the most coherent\nand understandable accounts"},{"time":2249162,"text":"about sentience, about consciousness,"},{"time":2251418,"text":"and that unique sort of human skill."},{"time":2254400,"text":"You point out that it's different\nfrom intelligence,"},{"time":2256917,"text":"the intelligence\nthat we're building in machines,"},{"time":2259275,"text":"and that there's actually a lot\nof mystery around it."},{"time":2262957,"text":"How can you be sure there's no purpose"},{"time":2266358,"text":"when we don't even understand\nwhat this sentience thing is?"},{"time":2270433,"text":"I mean, in your own thinking,\nisn't there a chance"},{"time":2273033,"text":"that what humans are for\nis to be the universe's sentient things,"},{"time":2277369,"text":"to be the centers of joy and love\nand happiness and hope?"},{"time":2280816,"text":"And maybe we can build machines\nthat actually help amplify that,"},{"time":2283875,"text":"even if they're not going to become\nsentient themselves?"},{"time":2286563,"text":"Is that crazy?"},{"time":2287738,"text":"I kind of found myself hoping that,\nreading your book."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2291245,"text":"YNH: Well, I certainly think that the most\ninteresting question today in science"},{"time":2295126,"text":"is the question\nof consciousness and the mind."},{"time":2297573,"text":"We are getting better and better\nin understanding the brain"},{"time":2301095,"text":"and intelligence,"},{"time":2302379,"text":"but we are not getting much better"},{"time":2304940,"text":"in understanding the mind\nand consciousness."},{"time":2307307,"text":"People often confuse intelligence\nand consciousness,"},{"time":2310693,"text":"especially in places like Silicon Valley,"},{"time":2313016,"text":"which is understandable,\nbecause in humans, they go together."},{"time":2316797,"text":"I mean, intelligence basically\nis the ability to solve problems."},{"time":2320400,"text":"Consciousness is the ability\nto feel things,"},{"time":2322966,"text":"to feel joy and sadness\nand boredom and pain and so forth."},{"time":2328202,"text":"In Homo sapiens and all other mammals\nas well -- it's not unique to humans --"},{"time":2332265,"text":"in all mammals and birds\nand some other animals,"},{"time":2334936,"text":"intelligence and consciousness\ngo together."},{"time":2337610,"text":"We often solve problems by feeling things."},{"time":2341212,"text":"So we tend to confuse them."},{"time":2342729,"text":"But they are different things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2344218,"text":"What's happening today\nin places like Silicon Valley"},{"time":2347330,"text":"is that we are creating\nartificial intelligence"},{"time":2350980,"text":"but not artificial consciousness."},{"time":2352826,"text":"There has been an amazing development\nin computer intelligence"},{"time":2356230,"text":"over the last 50 years,"},{"time":2357816,"text":"and exactly zero development\nin computer consciousness,"},{"time":2362041,"text":"and there is no indication that computers\nare going to become conscious"},{"time":2365751,"text":"anytime soon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2368306,"text":"So first of all, if there is\nsome cosmic role for consciousness,"},{"time":2373980,"text":"it's not unique to Homo sapiens."},{"time":2376134,"text":"Cows are conscious, pigs are conscious,"},{"time":2378477,"text":"chimpanzees are conscious,\nchickens are conscious,"},{"time":2381334,"text":"so if we go that way, first of all,\nwe need to broaden our horizons"},{"time":2385211,"text":"and remember very clearly we are not\nthe only sentient beings on Earth,"},{"time":2389960,"text":"and when it comes to sentience --"},{"time":2391779,"text":"when it comes to intelligence,\nthere is good reason to think"},{"time":2395115,"text":"we are the most intelligent\nof the whole bunch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2398435,"text":"But when it comes to sentience,"},{"time":2401033,"text":"to say that humans are more\nsentient than whales,"},{"time":2404215,"text":"or more sentient than baboons\nor more sentient than cats,"},{"time":2408386,"text":"I see no evidence for that."},{"time":2410704,"text":"So first step is, you go\nin that direction, expand."},{"time":2414335,"text":"And then the second question\nof what is it for,"},{"time":2418341,"text":"I would reverse it"},{"time":2420147,"text":"and I would say that I don't think\nsentience is for anything."},{"time":2424407,"text":"I think we don't need\nto find our role in the universe."},{"time":2428603,"text":"The really important thing\nis to liberate ourselves from suffering."},{"time":2434440,"text":"What characterizes sentient beings"},{"time":2437457,"text":"in contrast to robots, to stones,"},{"time":2440201,"text":"to whatever,"},{"time":2441408,"text":"is that sentient beings\nsuffer, can suffer,"},{"time":2445223,"text":"and what they should focus on"},{"time":2447587,"text":"is not finding their place\nin some mysterious cosmic drama."},{"time":2451731,"text":"They should focus on understanding\nwhat suffering is,"},{"time":2455574,"text":"what causes it and how\nto be liberated from it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2459572,"text":"CA: I know this is a big issue for you,\nand that was very eloquent."},{"time":2463073,"text":"We're going to have a blizzard\nof questions from the audience here,"},{"time":2466511,"text":"and maybe from Facebook as well,"},{"time":2468455,"text":"and maybe some comments as well."},{"time":2470152,"text":"So let's go quick."},{"time":2471972,"text":"There's one right here."},{"time":2475052,"text":"Keep your hands held up\nat the back if you want the mic,"},{"time":2477885,"text":"and we'll get it back to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2479328,"text":"Question: In your work, you talk a lot\nabout the fictional stories"},{"time":2482471,"text":"that we accept as truth,"},{"time":2483839,"text":"and we live our lives by it."},{"time":2485580,"text":"As an individual, knowing that,"},{"time":2488103,"text":"how does it impact the stories\nthat you choose to live your life,"},{"time":2491873,"text":"and do you confuse them\nwith the truth, like all of us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2496246,"text":"YNH: I try not to."},{"time":2497481,"text":"I mean, for me, maybe the most\nimportant question,"},{"time":2500273,"text":"both as a scientist and as a person,"},{"time":2502775,"text":"is how to tell the difference\nbetween fiction and reality,"},{"time":2506674,"text":"because reality is there."},{"time":2509294,"text":"I'm not saying that everything is fiction."},{"time":2511400,"text":"It's just very difficult for human beings\nto tell the difference"},{"time":2514476,"text":"between fiction and reality,"},{"time":2516117,"text":"and it has become more and more difficult\nas history progressed,"},{"time":2521086,"text":"because the fictions\nthat we have created --"},{"time":2523561,"text":"nations and gods and money\nand corporations --"},{"time":2526753,"text":"they now control the world."},{"time":2528287,"text":"So just to even think,"},{"time":2529488,"text":"\"Oh, this is just all fictional entities\nthat we've created,\""},{"time":2532657,"text":"is very difficult."},{"time":2534128,"text":"But reality is there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2537043,"text":"For me the best ..."},{"time":2539072,"text":"There are several tests"},{"time":2541219,"text":"to tell the difference\nbetween fiction and reality."},{"time":2544013,"text":"The simplest one, the best one\nthat I can say in short,"},{"time":2547463,"text":"is the test of suffering."},{"time":2549068,"text":"If it can suffer, it's real."},{"time":2551192,"text":"If it can't suffer, it's not real."},{"time":2552910,"text":"A nation cannot suffer."},{"time":2554399,"text":"That's very, very clear."},{"time":2555993,"text":"Even if a nation loses a war,"},{"time":2557955,"text":"we say, \"Germany suffered a defeat\nin the First World War,\""},{"time":2562044,"text":"it's a metaphor."},{"time":2563233,"text":"Germany cannot suffer.\nGermany has no mind."},{"time":2565814,"text":"Germany has no consciousness."},{"time":2567491,"text":"Germans can suffer, yes,\nbut Germany cannot."},{"time":2571173,"text":"Similarly, when a bank goes bust,"},{"time":2574166,"text":"the bank cannot suffer."},{"time":2575961,"text":"When the dollar loses its value,\nthe dollar doesn't suffer."},{"time":2579376,"text":"People can suffer. Animals can suffer."},{"time":2581650,"text":"This is real."},{"time":2582830,"text":"So I would start, if you\nreally want to see reality,"},{"time":2587383,"text":"I would go through the door of suffering."},{"time":2589471,"text":"If you can really understand\nwhat suffering is,"},{"time":2592449,"text":"this will give you also the key"},{"time":2594696,"text":"to understand what reality is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2596737,"text":"CA: There's a Facebook question\nhere that connects to this,"},{"time":2599544,"text":"from someone around the world\nin a language that I cannot read."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2602545,"text":"YNH: Oh, it's Hebrew.\nCA: Hebrew. There you go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2604786,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2605872,"text":"Can you read the name?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2607060,"text":"YNH: Or Lauterbach Goren."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2608959,"text":"CA: Well, thank you for writing in."},{"time":2610827,"text":"The question is: \"Is the post-truth era\nreally a brand-new era,"},{"time":2615406,"text":"or just another climax or moment\nin a never-ending trend?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2620701,"text":"YNH: Personally, I don't connect\nwith this idea of post-truth."},{"time":2624054,"text":"My basic reaction as a historian is:"},{"time":2626786,"text":"If this is the era of post-truth,\nwhen the hell was the era of truth?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2630705,"text":"CA: Right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2631980,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2633324,"text":"YNH: Was it the 1980s, the 1950s,\nthe Middle Ages?"},{"time":2638031,"text":"I mean, we have always lived\nin an era, in a way, of post-truth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2642883,"text":"CA: But I'd push back on that,"},{"time":2645218,"text":"because I think what people\nare talking about"},{"time":2647912,"text":"is that there was a world\nwhere you had fewer journalistic outlets,"},{"time":2654896,"text":"where there were traditions,\nthat things were fact-checked."},{"time":2658568,"text":"It was incorporated into the charter\nof those organizations"},{"time":2662537,"text":"that the truth mattered."},{"time":2664728,"text":"So if you believe in a reality,"},{"time":2666501,"text":"then what you write is information."},{"time":2668748,"text":"There was a belief that that information\nshould connect to reality in a real way,"},{"time":2672593,"text":"and if you wrote a headline,\nit was a serious, earnest attempt"},{"time":2675578,"text":"to reflect something\nthat had actually happened."},{"time":2677905,"text":"And people didn't always get it right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2679780,"text":"But I think the concern now is you've got"},{"time":2681813,"text":"a technological system\nthat's incredibly powerful"},{"time":2684155,"text":"that, for a while at least,\nmassively amplified anything"},{"time":2688349,"text":"with no attention paid to whether\nit connected to reality,"},{"time":2691153,"text":"only to whether it connected\nto clicks and attention,"},{"time":2694331,"text":"and that that was arguably toxic."},{"time":2695971,"text":"That's a reasonable concern, isn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2698431,"text":"YNH: Yeah, it is. I mean,\nthe technology changes,"},{"time":2700741,"text":"and it's now easier to disseminate\nboth truth and fiction and falsehood."},{"time":2705993,"text":"It goes both ways."},{"time":2708020,"text":"It's also much easier, though, to spread\nthe truth than it was ever before."},{"time":2712623,"text":"But I don't think there\nis anything essentially new"},{"time":2716332,"text":"about this disseminating\nfictions and errors."},{"time":2721076,"text":"There is nothing that -- I don't know --\nJoseph Goebbels, didn't know"},{"time":2725134,"text":"about all this idea of fake\nnews and post-truth."},{"time":2730597,"text":"He famously said that if you repeat\na lie often enough,"},{"time":2734339,"text":"people will think it's the truth,"},{"time":2736184,"text":"and the bigger the lie, the better,"},{"time":2738564,"text":"because people won't even think\nthat something so big can be a lie."},{"time":2744611,"text":"I think that fake news\nhas been with us for thousands of years."},{"time":2750293,"text":"Just think of the Bible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2752218,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2753629,"text":"CA: But there is a concern"},{"time":2754940,"text":"that the fake news is associated\nwith tyrannical regimes,"},{"time":2758981,"text":"and when you see an uprise in fake news"},{"time":2761582,"text":"that is a canary in the coal mine\nthat there may be dark times coming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2768124,"text":"YNH: Yeah. I mean, the intentional use\nof fake news is a disturbing sign."},{"time":2775812,"text":"But I'm not saying that it's not bad,\nI'm just saying that it's not new."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2780820,"text":"CA: There's a lot of interest\non Facebook on this question"},{"time":2783598,"text":"about global governance\nversus nationalism."},{"time":2789292,"text":"Question here from Phil Dennis:"},{"time":2790824,"text":"\"How do we get people, governments,\nto relinquish power?"},{"time":2794344,"text":"Is that -- is that --\nactually, the text is so big"},{"time":2798283,"text":"I can't read the full question."},{"time":2799847,"text":"But is that a necessity?"},{"time":2801410,"text":"Is it going to take war to get there?"},{"time":2804046,"text":"Sorry Phil -- I mangled your question,\nbut I blame the text right here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2807760,"text":"YNH: One option\nthat some people talk about"},{"time":2809884,"text":"is that only a catastrophe\ncan shake humankind"},{"time":2814647,"text":"and open the path to a real system\nof global governance,"},{"time":2819935,"text":"and they say that we can't do it\nbefore the catastrophe,"},{"time":2824107,"text":"but we need to start\nlaying the foundations"},{"time":2826932,"text":"so that when the disaster strikes,"},{"time":2829456,"text":"we can react quickly."},{"time":2831662,"text":"But people will just not have\nthe motivation to do such a thing"},{"time":2835686,"text":"before the disaster strikes."},{"time":2837722,"text":"Another thing that I would emphasize"},{"time":2840011,"text":"is that anybody who is really\ninterested in global governance"},{"time":2845089,"text":"should always make it very, very clear"},{"time":2848014,"text":"that it doesn't replace or abolish\nlocal identities and communities,"},{"time":2854622,"text":"that it should come both as --"},{"time":2857602,"text":"It should be part of a single package."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2860933,"text":"CA: I want to hear more on this,"},{"time":2864335,"text":"because the very words \"global governance\""},{"time":2867412,"text":"are almost the epitome of evil\nin the mindset of a lot of people"},{"time":2872025,"text":"on the alt-right right now."},{"time":2873375,"text":"It just seems scary, remote, distant,\nand it has let them down,"},{"time":2876353,"text":"and so globalists,\nglobal governance -- no, go away!"},{"time":2880493,"text":"And many view the election\nas the ultimate poke in the eye"},{"time":2884199,"text":"to anyone who believes in that."},{"time":2885701,"text":"So how do we change the narrative"},{"time":2889276,"text":"so that it doesn't seem\nso scary and remote?"},{"time":2892275,"text":"Build more on this idea\nof it being compatible"},{"time":2895043,"text":"with local identity, local communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2897688,"text":"YNH: Well, I think again we should start"},{"time":2900312,"text":"really with the biological realities"},{"time":2903468,"text":"of Homo sapiens."},{"time":2905503,"text":"And biology tells us two things\nabout Homo sapiens"},{"time":2909645,"text":"which are very relevant to this issue:"},{"time":2911926,"text":"first of all, that we are\ncompletely dependent"},{"time":2914979,"text":"on the ecological system around us,"},{"time":2917598,"text":"and that today we are talking\nabout a global system."},{"time":2921081,"text":"You cannot escape that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2922462,"text":"And at the same time, biology tells us\nabout Homo sapiens"},{"time":2926108,"text":"that we are social animals,"},{"time":2928379,"text":"but that we are social\non a very, very local level."},{"time":2933040,"text":"It's just a simple fact of humanity"},{"time":2936609,"text":"that we cannot have intimate familiarity"},{"time":2941430,"text":"with more than about 150 individuals."},{"time":2945329,"text":"The size of the natural group,"},{"time":2949650,"text":"the natural community of Homo sapiens,"},{"time":2952776,"text":"is not more than 150 individuals,"},{"time":2956144,"text":"and everything beyond that is really\nbased on all kinds of imaginary stories"},{"time":2962567,"text":"and large-scale institutions,"},{"time":2964638,"text":"and I think that we can find a way,"},{"time":2969038,"text":"again, based on a biological\nunderstanding of our species,"},{"time":2973632,"text":"to weave the two together"},{"time":2975738,"text":"and to understand that today\nin the 21st century,"},{"time":2978838,"text":"we need both the global level\nand the local community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2984398,"text":"And I would go even further than that"},{"time":2986439,"text":"and say that it starts\nwith the body itself."},{"time":2990500,"text":"The feelings that people today have\nof alienation and loneliness"},{"time":2994866,"text":"and not finding their place in the world,"},{"time":2998106,"text":"I would think that the chief problem\nis not global capitalism."},{"time":3004285,"text":"The chief problem is that over\nthe last hundred years,"},{"time":3007335,"text":"people have been becoming disembodied,"},{"time":3011063,"text":"have been distancing themselves\nfrom their body."},{"time":3014246,"text":"As a hunter-gatherer or even as a peasant,"},{"time":3017166,"text":"to survive, you need to be\nconstantly in touch"},{"time":3021388,"text":"with your body and with your senses,"},{"time":3023595,"text":"every moment."},{"time":3024800,"text":"If you go to the forest\nto look for mushrooms"},{"time":3026971,"text":"and you don't pay attention\nto what you hear,"},{"time":3029372,"text":"to what you smell, to what you taste,"},{"time":3031272,"text":"you're dead."},{"time":3032447,"text":"So you must be very connected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3034622,"text":"In the last hundred years,\npeople are losing their ability"},{"time":3039242,"text":"to be in touch with their body\nand their senses,"},{"time":3042138,"text":"to hear, to smell, to feel."},{"time":3044348,"text":"More and more attention goes to screens,"},{"time":3047498,"text":"to what is happening elsewhere,"},{"time":3049042,"text":"some other time."},{"time":3050287,"text":"This, I think, is the deep reason"},{"time":3052742,"text":"for the feelings of alienation\nand loneliness and so forth,"},{"time":3056660,"text":"and therefore part of the solution"},{"time":3059186,"text":"is not to bring back\nsome mass nationalism,"},{"time":3063474,"text":"but also reconnect with our own bodies,"},{"time":3067622,"text":"and if you are back\nin touch with your body,"},{"time":3070909,"text":"you will feel much more at home\nin the world also."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3074103,"text":"CA: Well, depending on how things go,\nwe may all be back in the forest soon."},{"time":3077812,"text":"We're going to have\none more question in the room"},{"time":3080185,"text":"and one more on Facebook."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3081712,"text":"Ama Adi-Dako: Hello. I'm from Ghana,\nWest Africa, and my question is:"},{"time":3085117,"text":"I'm wondering how do you present\nand justify the idea of global governance"},{"time":3089743,"text":"to countries that have been\nhistorically disenfranchised"},{"time":3092778,"text":"by the effects of globalization,"},{"time":3094847,"text":"and also, if we're talking about\nglobal governance,"},{"time":3097617,"text":"it sounds to me like it will definitely\ncome from a very Westernized idea"},{"time":3101265,"text":"of what the \"global\"\nis supposed to look like."},{"time":3103463,"text":"So how do we present and justify\nthat idea of global"},{"time":3106777,"text":"versus wholly nationalist"},{"time":3109794,"text":"to people in countries like Ghana\nand Nigeria and Togo"},{"time":3113153,"text":"and other countries like that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":3116131,"text":"YNH: I would start by saying\nthat history is extremely unfair,"},{"time":3122569,"text":"and that we should realize that."},{"time":3127004,"text":"Many of the countries that suffered most"},{"time":3130077,"text":"from the last 200 years of globalization"},{"time":3134240,"text":"and imperialism and industrialization"},{"time":3136224,"text":"are exactly the countries\nwhich are also most likely to suffer most"},{"time":3141958,"text":"from the next wave."},{"time":3144771,"text":"And we should be very,\nvery clear about that."},{"time":3149477,"text":"If we don't have a global governance,"},{"time":3152552,"text":"and if we suffer from climate change,"},{"time":3155779,"text":"from technological disruptions,"},{"time":3158060,"text":"the worst suffering will not be in the US."},{"time":3161685,"text":"The worst suffering will be in Ghana,\nwill be in Sudan, will be in Syria,"},{"time":3166805,"text":"will be in Bangladesh,\nwill be in those places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3169566,"text":"So I think those countries\nhave an even greater incentive"},{"time":3175626,"text":"to do something about\nthe next wave of disruption,"},{"time":3180377,"text":"whether it's ecological\nor whether it's technological."},{"time":3182926,"text":"Again, if you think about\ntechnological disruption,"},{"time":3185796,"text":"so if AI and 3D printers and robots\nwill take the jobs"},{"time":3190436,"text":"from billions of people,"},{"time":3192829,"text":"I worry far less about the Swedes"},{"time":3195978,"text":"than about the people in Ghana\nor in Bangladesh."},{"time":3199607,"text":"And therefore,\nbecause history is so unfair"},{"time":3204859,"text":"and the results of a calamity"},{"time":3209229,"text":"will not be shared equally\nbetween everybody,"},{"time":3211621,"text":"as usual, the rich\nwill be able to get away"},{"time":3216078,"text":"from the worst consequences\nof climate change"},{"time":3219574,"text":"in a way that the poor\nwill not be able to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3223347,"text":"CA: And here's a great question\nfrom Cameron Taylor on Facebook:"},{"time":3226779,"text":"\"At the end of 'Sapiens,'\""},{"time":3228924,"text":"you said we should be asking the question,"},{"time":3231011,"text":"'What do we want to want?'"},{"time":3233391,"text":"Well, what do you think\nwe should want to want?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":3236402,"text":"YNH: I think we should want\nto want to know the truth,"},{"time":3239957,"text":"to understand reality."},{"time":3243207,"text":"Mostly what we want is to change reality,"},{"time":3248345,"text":"to fit it to our own desires,\nto our own wishes,"},{"time":3252087,"text":"and I think we should first\nwant to understand it."},{"time":3255831,"text":"If you look at the long-term\ntrajectory of history,"},{"time":3259619,"text":"what you see is that\nfor thousands of years"},{"time":3262379,"text":"we humans have been gaining\ncontrol of the world outside us"},{"time":3265739,"text":"and trying to shape it\nto fit our own desires."},{"time":3269257,"text":"And we've gained control\nof the other animals,"},{"time":3272469,"text":"of the rivers, of the forests,"},{"time":3274024,"text":"and reshaped them completely,"},{"time":3277541,"text":"causing an ecological destruction"},{"time":3280926,"text":"without making ourselves satisfied."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3284128,"text":"So the next step\nis we turn our gaze inwards,"},{"time":3287954,"text":"and we say OK, getting control\nof the world outside us"},{"time":3292526,"text":"did not really make us satisfied."},{"time":3294414,"text":"Let's now try to gain control\nof the world inside us."},{"time":3297137,"text":"This is the really big project"},{"time":3299324,"text":"of science and technology\nand industry in the 21st century --"},{"time":3303644,"text":"to try and gain control\nof the world inside us,"},{"time":3307190,"text":"to learn how to engineer and produce\nbodies and brains and minds."},{"time":3312137,"text":"These are likely to be the main\nproducts of the 21st century economy."},{"time":3316803,"text":"When people think about the future,\nvery often they think in terms,"},{"time":3320648,"text":"\"Oh, I want to gain control\nof my body and of my brain.\""},{"time":3324619,"text":"And I think that's very dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3327453,"text":"If we've learned anything\nfrom our previous history,"},{"time":3330743,"text":"it's that yes, we gain\nthe power to manipulate,"},{"time":3334680,"text":"but because we didn't really\nunderstand the complexity"},{"time":3337494,"text":"of the ecological system,"},{"time":3339323,"text":"we are now facing an ecological meltdown."},{"time":3343037,"text":"And if we now try to reengineer\nthe world inside us"},{"time":3348467,"text":"without really understanding it,"},{"time":3350623,"text":"especially without understanding\nthe complexity of our mental system,"},{"time":3354963,"text":"we might cause a kind of internal\necological disaster,"},{"time":3359647,"text":"and we'll face a kind of mental\nmeltdown inside us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3364270,"text":"CA: Putting all the pieces\ntogether here --"},{"time":3366736,"text":"the current politics,\nthe coming technology,"},{"time":3369440,"text":"concerns like the one\nyou've just outlined --"},{"time":3371614,"text":"I mean, it seems like you yourself\nare in quite a bleak place"},{"time":3374733,"text":"when you think about the future."},{"time":3376378,"text":"You're pretty worried about it."},{"time":3377984,"text":"Is that right?"},{"time":3379200,"text":"And if there was one cause for hope,\nhow would you state that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":3385912,"text":"YNH: I focus on the most\ndangerous possibilities"},{"time":3390099,"text":"partly because this is like\nmy job or responsibility"},{"time":3393144,"text":"as a historian or social critic."},{"time":3394949,"text":"I mean, the industry focuses mainly\non the positive sides,"},{"time":3399735,"text":"so it's the job of historians\nand philosophers and sociologists"},{"time":3403120,"text":"to highlight the more dangerous potential\nof all these new technologies."},{"time":3407585,"text":"I don't think any of that is inevitable."},{"time":3410092,"text":"Technology is never deterministic."},{"time":3413155,"text":"You can use the same technology"},{"time":3414896,"text":"to create very different\nkinds of societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3417911,"text":"If you look at the 20th century,"},{"time":3419973,"text":"so, the technologies\nof the Industrial Revolution,"},{"time":3422778,"text":"the trains and electricity and all that"},{"time":3425859,"text":"could be used to create\na communist dictatorship"},{"time":3428935,"text":"or a fascist regime\nor a liberal democracy."},{"time":3431764,"text":"The trains did not tell you\nwhat to do with them."},{"time":3434316,"text":"Similarly, now, artificial intelligence\nand bioengineering and all of that --"},{"time":3438792,"text":"they don't predetermine a single outcome."},{"time":3442886,"text":"Humanity can rise up to the challenge,"},{"time":3446087,"text":"and the best example we have"},{"time":3447802,"text":"of humanity rising up\nto the challenge of a new technology"},{"time":3451566,"text":"is nuclear weapons."},{"time":3453313,"text":"In the late 1940s, '50s,"},{"time":3456346,"text":"many people were convinced"},{"time":3458509,"text":"that sooner or later the Cold War\nwill end in a nuclear catastrophe,"},{"time":3462839,"text":"destroying human civilization."},{"time":3464638,"text":"And this did not happen."},{"time":3466142,"text":"In fact, nuclear weapons prompted\nhumans all over the world"},{"time":3472586,"text":"to change the way that they manage\ninternational politics"},{"time":3477351,"text":"to reduce violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3479744,"text":"And many countries basically took out war"},{"time":3483007,"text":"from their political toolkit."},{"time":3484905,"text":"They no longer tried to pursue\ntheir interests with warfare."},{"time":3489580,"text":"Not all countries have done so,\nbut many countries have."},{"time":3492874,"text":"And this is maybe\nthe most important reason"},{"time":3496832,"text":"why international violence\ndeclined dramatically since 1945,"},{"time":3502958,"text":"and today, as I said,\nmore people commit suicide"},{"time":3506320,"text":"than are killed in war."},{"time":3508551,"text":"So this, I think, gives us a good example"},{"time":3513404,"text":"that even the most frightening technology,"},{"time":3517270,"text":"humans can rise up to the challenge"},{"time":3519829,"text":"and actually some good can come out of it."},{"time":3522876,"text":"The problem is, we have very little\nmargin for error."},{"time":3527187,"text":"If we don't get it right,"},{"time":3529420,"text":"we might not have\na second option to try again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3534337,"text":"CA: That's a very powerful note,"},{"time":3535928,"text":"on which I think we should draw\nthis to a conclusion."},{"time":3538757,"text":"Before I wrap up, I just want to say\none thing to people here"},{"time":3541892,"text":"and to the global TED community\nwatching online, anyone watching online:"},{"time":3547462,"text":"help us with these dialogues."},{"time":3550379,"text":"If you believe, like we do,"},{"time":3552953,"text":"that we need to find\na different kind of conversation,"},{"time":3555957,"text":"now more than ever, help us do it."},{"time":3558214,"text":"Reach out to other people,"},{"time":3561269,"text":"try and have conversations\nwith people you disagree with,"},{"time":3564033,"text":"understand them,"},{"time":3565240,"text":"pull the pieces together,"},{"time":3566794,"text":"and help us figure out how to take\nthese conversations forward"},{"time":3570710,"text":"so we can make a real contribution"},{"time":3572988,"text":"to what's happening\nin the world right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3575757,"text":"I think everyone feels more alive,"},{"time":3579100,"text":"more concerned, more engaged"},{"time":3581434,"text":"with the politics of the moment."},{"time":3583987,"text":"The stakes do seem quite high,"},{"time":3586465,"text":"so help us respond to it\nin a wise, wise way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3591001,"text":"Yuval Harari, thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3592620,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}